quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  17,39,"That is some of the wisdom your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord has revealed to you. And do not set up with Allah another god, lest you be thrown in Hell, blamed, banished."
  17,40,"Has your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>Lord favored you with sons and taken for Himself from the angels females? You<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>are certainly saying a great{1}saying.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word azeemis sometimes used with a negative connotation to denote the seriousness of a matter.
  17,41,"And very truly, We have explained in this Recital{1}in various ways, that they may <span class=""h"">constantly remember<sup foot_note=""80435"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span>, but it only adds to their aversion.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Qur’an which literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  17,42,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “If there were other gods with Him as <span class=""h"">they<sup foot_note=""80436"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">say</span>, they would have sought a way to the Possessor of the Throne.”"
  17,43,"Highly Exalted is He. He is Most High, far above what they say."
  17,44,"Exalting Him are the seven heavens and the earth and whoever is in them. And there is not a thing that does not exalt Him with praise, but you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>do not comprehend their exaltation. Indeed, He has always been Forbearing, Oft-Forgiving."
  17,45,"And when you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>recite the Recital{1}, We place between you and those who do not believe in the Hereafter an invisible barrier.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Qur’an which literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  17,46,"And We have placed veils over their hearts preventing them from comprehending it, and heaviness in their ears. And when you mention your Lord{1}alone in the Recital<a class=""sup""><sup>a </sup></a>, they turn their backs in aversion.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 1st person to 3rd person.
  17,47,"We know better what<i class=""s"">(intention) </i>it is that they listen with as they listen to you and as they secretly converse, as the unjust say, “You<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>are following nothing but a man bewitched.”"
  17,48,"Look<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>at how they have set forth parables for you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>and gone astray, so they cannot find a way."
  17,49,"And they said, “<span class=""h"">Can it be that</span>when we have become bones and fragments—<span class=""h"">can it be that<sup foot_note=""80439"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>we will really be resurrected as a new creation?”"
